Quick production-safe fix

Instead of calculating yourself, force a minimum top position:

function onStockCodedPartEdit(e) {

    var wnd = e.container.data("kendoWindow");

    if (!wnd) return;

    setTimeout(function () {

        var wrapper = wnd.wrapper;

        var left = ($(window).width() - wrapper.outerWidth()) / 2;
        var top = ($(window).height() - wrapper.outerHeight()) / 2;

        wrapper.css({
            left: Math.max(20, left) + "px",
            top: Math.max(20, top) + "px"
        });

    }, 50);
}
Even simpler test

While popup is open, run:

$(".k-window.scparts-popup-style").css({
    top: "80px",
    left: "50%"
});

then:

$(".k-window.scparts-popup-style").css(
    "margin-left",
    -($(".k-window.scparts-popup-style").outerWidth() / 2) + "px"
);

If it immediately jumps to the visual center, then we know the issue is 100% positioning, not sizing.

